A motorcyclist, believed to be in his 40s, was killed when his motorbike crashed into a truck on Houtkop Road near Voortrekker Street in Vereeniging in Gauteng in the early hours of Sunday morning, paramedics said.
When ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene shortly after 1.30am, they found the provincial emergency medical services (EMS) already in attendance, ER24 spokeswoman Ineke van Huyssteen said.
“Upon further assessment, it was found that the motorbike rider sustained fatal injuries and the provincial EMS declared the man dead at the scene.”
The circumstances surrounding the accident were not known, Van Huyssteen said.
– African News Agency (ANA)